9. Bxc4
9. Bg4{ Best, as it creates some pressure on the isolated pawn. }
10. Be3{ Easily the most popular move in this position in practice. }( {  A)  }10.h3 Bxf3 { We are obliged to capture to not lose time. }11.Qxf3 Nc6 12.Rd1 Ne8 { This went well for Black following 0-1 (59) Andrijevic,M (2325)-Radlovacki,J (2425) Belgrade 2013. The knight will land on  d6  and potentially  f5  to pressure the  d -pawn. } )( {  B)  }10.d5 Nbd7 { As the best square has been taken away, we will simply develop with the next best option. }11.Re1 Rc8 12.Bb3 Nc5 { The position is balanced, but trades favor the player playing against the isolated pawn. Black objectively has the easier position to play following 0-1 (47) Dashiev,K (2041) -Dondukov,S (2344) Ulan-Ude 2015. } )
